          "text" : "asyncValues",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "TinkoffConcurrency provides a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/combine\/publisher\/values-v7nz",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "alternative which allows you to use the Swift ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "async",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "-",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "await",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " syntax to receive the publisher’s elements.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It follows Apple’s ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/combine\/publisher\/values-v7nz",
              "isActive" : true,
              "overridingTitle" : "Publisher.values",
              "overridingTitleInlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Publisher.values",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " contract, but is",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "available on earlier OS versions.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example shows how to use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "asyncValues",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property to receive elements asynchronously.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The example adapts a code snippet from the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/combine\/publisher\/filter(_:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " operator’s documentation,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "which filters a sequence to only emit even integers. This example replaces the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/combine\/subscribers\/sink",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "subscriber with a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "for",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "-",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "await",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "-",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "in",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " loop that iterates over the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/TinkoffConcurrency\/documentation\/TinkoffConcurrency\/TCAsyncPublisher",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "provided by the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "asyncValues",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "    let numbers: [Int] = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]",
            "    let filtered = numbers.publisher",
            "        .filter { $0 % 2 == 0 }",
            "",
            "    for await number in filtered.asyncValues",
            "    {",
            "        print(\"\\(number)\", terminator: \" \")",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Async-Channel",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Async Channel",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In addition to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "asyncValues",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", which is Combine → Swift Concurrency bridge, Tinkoff Concurrency provides another",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "one that allows sending data from Swift Concurrency to Combine respecting Combine’s backpressure. We call it ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/TinkoffConcurrency\/documentation\/TinkoffConcurrency\/TCAsyncChannel",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Basically, this contract is borrowed from Apple Async Algorithms ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-async-algorithms\/blob\/main\/Sources\/AsyncAlgorithms\/AsyncAlgorithms.docc\/Guides\/Channel.md",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "behavior. Consider the following example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "    let subject = PassthroughSubject<String, Error>()",
            "",
            "    Task {",
            "        while let value = getValue() {",
            "            subject.send(value)",
            "        }",
            "",
            "        subject.send(completion: .finished)",
            "    }",
            "",
            "    for await value in subject.asyncValues {",
            "        await useValue(value)",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "getValue()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is executed fast enough, we can lose some values, because ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PassthroughSubject",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " would drop them until",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "subscription is ready to receive. Fortunately, in async context, we can use Combine’s backpressure mechanism to synchronize",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "reader and writer. In the next example, no values would be lost, because ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/TinkoffConcurrency\/documentation\/TinkoffConcurrency\/TCAsyncChannel\/send(_:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " will wait until",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "there’s at least one subscriber, and all subscribers are ready to receive a value.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "    let channel = TCAsyncChannel<String, Error>()",
            "",
            "    Task {",
            "        while let value = getValue() {",
            "            try await channel.send(value)",
            "        }",
            "",
            "        try channel.send(completion: .finished)",
            "    }",
            "",
            "    for await value in channel.asyncValues {",
            "        await useValue(value)",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This way, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/TinkoffConcurrency\/documentation\/TinkoffConcurrency\/TCAsyncChannel",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " can be used as a synchronization primitive like Golang ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "chan",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-async-algorithms\/blob\/main\/Sources\/AsyncAlgorithms\/AsyncAlgorithms.docc\/Guides\/Channel.md",
              "isActive" : true,
              "overridingTitle" : "AsyncChannel",
              "overridingTitleInlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "AsyncChannel",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "reference"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Bear in mind, however, that there still could be race conditions. In example below, some initial values could be skipped by one of the readers,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "depending on when subscription is scheduled. But, when both subscriptions are estabilished, next value could be submitted only when previous value",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is consumed by both of the readers.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "    let channel = TCAsyncChannel<String, Error>()",
            "",
            "    Task {",
            "        while let value = getValue() {",
            "            try await channel.send(value)",
            "        }",
            "",
            "        try channel.send(completion: .finished)",
            "    }",
            "",
            "    Task {",
            "        for await value in channel.asyncValues {",
            "            await doSomething(with: value)",
            "        }",
            "    }",
            "",
            "    Task {",
            "        for await value in channel.asyncValues {",
            "            await doSomethingElse(with: value)",
            "        }",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
